15#ifndef ISC_EVENTCLASS_H
16#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_H 1
17
18/*! \file isc/eventclass.h
19 ***** Registry of Predefined Event Type Classes
20 *****/
21
22/*%
23 * An event class is an unsigned 16 bit number. Each class may contain up
24 * to 65536 events. An event type is formed by adding the event number
25 * within the class to the class number.
26 *
27 */
28
29#define ISC_EVENTCLASS(eclass) ((eclass) << 16)
30
31/*@{*/
32/*!
33 * Classes < 1024 are reserved for ISC use.
34 * Event classes >= 1024 and <= 65535 are reserved for application use.
35 */
36
37#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_TASK ISC_EVENTCLASS(0)
38#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_TIMER ISC_EVENTCLASS(1)
39#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_SOCKET ISC_EVENTCLASS(2)
40#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_FILE ISC_EVENTCLASS(3)
41#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_DNS ISC_EVENTCLASS(4)
42#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_APP ISC_EVENTCLASS(5)
43#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_OMAPI ISC_EVENTCLASS(6)
44#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_RATELIMITER ISC_EVENTCLASS(7)
45#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_ISCCC ISC_EVENTCLASS(8)
46#define ISC_EVENTCLASS_NS ISC_EVENTCLASS(9)
47/*@}*/
48
49#endif /* ISC_EVENTCLASS_H */
50
